p"},{"type":"text","value":"We can load the data lazily (only loading the metadata and coordinates information) and peek at the data's dimension and availability on our local machine. The actual data (SST values at each grid point in this case) will only be downloaded from the PSL server when further data manipulation (subsetting and aggregation like calculating mean) is needed. The only thing user needs to do to activate this function is to read the netCDF file using the `xr.open_dataset()` method with the keyword argument `chunks={'time':12,'lon':-1,'lat':-1}` provided. The chunk reading approach provide the opportunity to reduce the memory usage on the local machine during the calculation, the possibility of parallelizing the processes, and side-stepping the data download limit set by the OPeNDAP server (PSL server has a 500MB limit). The dataset is loaded lazily (only metadata and coordinates) shown below.","key":"TNtn0pcwPC"}],"key":"sBJCdBez8w"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In our example, we set the size of each chunk to be 12(time)x1440(lon)x720(lat) (when setting the chunk size = -1, it will use the length of the dimension as the chunksize) which is equal to 47.46 MB of data while the entire dataset is 1.39 GB.\nThis allows us to get data in 47.46 MB chunk per download request.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"key":"rqyAX2DrVC"}],"key":"JaoY87IJsr"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The dataset is loaded lazily (only metadata and coordinates) shown below.","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"D4iUVKA5gJ"}],"key":"vQ2VFEUmGG"}],"key":"wCtmfrLC6v"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"ds_mon","visibility":"show","key":"mwqHleSL6Q"},{"type":"output","id":"-oPrBAnyTVO1bJuH88ESN","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"sr0Dz66S2R"}],"visibility":"show","key":"F07uKtpoUu"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Calculate the SST climatology","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"BV0qQtx3pF"}],"identifier":"calculate-the-sst-climatology","label":"Calculate the SST climatology","html_id":"calculate-the-sst-climatology","implicit":true,"key":"BgViLkBHdd"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"First, we need to define the period that we are going to use to calculate the climatology.\nHere, we picked the 2019-2020 period to calculate the climatology.","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"key":"o3STz5T8JD"}],"key":"Uqyt4b4S0j"},{"type":"div","class":"admonition alert alert-warning","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Climatology","key":"aNGAJWUA9Y"}],"key":"QGLf4FHEu1"},{"type":"text","value":"For a more accurate and scientifically valid estimate of marine heatwaves, one should usually consider a climatology period of at least 30 years. Here we set the climatology period from 2019 to 2020 (2 years) to speed up the processing time and for demonstration only. The shorter period (less memory consumption) also makes the interactive notebook launch on this page available for the user to manipulate and play with the dataset.","key":"VDbU0p4umN"}],"key":"zmfAe2VRGL"}],"key":"LREFU00c7s"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"climo_start_yr = 2019             # determine the climatology/linear trend start year\nclimo_end_yr = 2020               # determine the climatology/linear trend end year\n\nds_mon_crop = ds_mon.where((ds_mon['time.year']>=climo_start_yr)&\n                           (ds_mon['time.year']<=climo_end_yr),drop=True)","visibility":"show","key":"VIHW3FLoiC"},{"type":"output","id":"aK84uCqUAMI9cCISgDtxu","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"twtXKrx0af"}],"visibility":"show","key":"bdxhgajbtb"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"ds_mon_crop","visibility":"show","key":"C20pWSLfN4"},{"type":"output","id":"o3NZQZLu9L3s8A4APzEnO","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"cnWNE6YRPt"}],"visibility":"show","key":"a2ZwDUgx3w"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To calculate the SST monthly climatology, we utilize the ","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"Xz12vz3C1Z"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"groupby","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"LMVdheqeeR"},{"type":"text","value":" method from Xarray.","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"IvPIc8P5tU"}],"key":"OIhAXrYGSQ"}],"key":"a5oCHKwWye"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"ds_mon_climo = ds_mon_crop.groupby('time.month').mean()","visibility":"show","key":"Jx7v86WGwk"},{"type":"output","id":"nmlCyipG0cmzLxDpgZwMT","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"QFfroq18rN"}],"visibility":"show","key":"lX8qYYQ6VZ"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Calculate the SST anomaly","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"m29xjFzViI"}],"identifier":"calculate-the-sst-anomaly","label":"Calculate the SST anomaly","html_id":"calculate-the-sst-anomaly","implicit":true,"key":"jTRDAARhNp"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After the climatology is determined, we subtract the climatology from the original data to get the anomaly.","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"key":"JYY1roJ1GK"}],"key":"U8TGmz63p1"}],"key":"YM1XMbmOrN"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"ds_mon_anom = (ds_mon_crop.groupby('time.month')-ds_mon_climo).compute()","visibility":"show","key":"DPlj3AAw78"},{"type":"output","id":"5hovcOz0gCXTHuwM-Brll","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"EmmjYAGESb"}],"visibility":"show","key":"yroV00EC31"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"div","class":"admonition alert alert-success","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":".compute()","key":"NkLSTVy4zm"}],"key":"pd9clUNTnB"},{"type":"text","value":"Notice the `.compute()` method in the code above. The data of SST is only loaded chunk-by-chunk, cropped to the desired period, averaged in the group of months, and finally subtracted the climatology from the original data when we execute the `.compute()` line. All these tasks are now executed in the background with a distributed server assigning tasks to different CPUs.","key":"bVzhy8AWUH"}],"key":"QUyX9JqErI"}],"key":"DjRlAt7f71"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"ds_mon_anom","visibility":"show","key":"sU8ljhPhMX"},{"type":"output","id":"5UFpNk67tVZQo3GLGr-Af","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"ia0DDECeVK"}],"visibility":"show","key":"gbfoLbHw2H"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Determine the SST threshold based on the anomaly","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"ykIg6Xhe8R"}],"identifier":"determine-the-sst-threshold-based-on-the-anomaly","label":"Determine the SST threshold based on the anomaly","html_id":"determine-the-sst-threshold-based-on-the-anomaly","implicit":true,"key":"KPhxBJHvUf"}],"key":"tqI0W4njpb"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Based on the ","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"b9kNrZ4NQN"},{"type":"cite","url":"http://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-022-04573-9","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Jacox et al., 2022","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"MWRT55dsdx"}],"kind":"narrative","label":"Jacox_2022","identifier":"http://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-022-04573-9","enumerator":"1","key":"WeQtSv3XEU"},{"type":"text","value":", the threshold is determined based on a three month window with the center month being the monthly threhold one need to determined (e.g. January threshold is determined by all December, January, Feburary SST anomalies).\nTherefore, the function below is written to perform the three months window percentile operation.","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"MGKC6cawGk"}],"key":"LLUFJYGLLo"}],"key":"xs7Sm7vk29"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"########## Functions ######### \n# Function to calculate the 3 month rolling Quantile\ndef mj_3mon_quantile(da_data, mhw_threshold=90.):\n    \n    da_data_quantile = xr.DataArray(coords={'lon':da_data.lon,\n                                            'lat':da_data.lat,\n                                            'month':np.arange(1,13)},\n                                    dims = ['month','lat','lon'])\n\n    for i in range(1,13):\n        if i == 1:\n            mon_range = [12,1,2]\n        elif i == 12 :\n            mon_range = [11,12,1]\n        else:\n            mon_range = [i-1,i,i+1]\n\n        da_data_quantile[i-1,:,:] = (da_data\n                                 .where((da_data['time.month'] == mon_range[0])|\n                                        (da_data['time.month'] == mon_range[1])|\n                                        (da_data['time.month'] == mon_range[2]),drop=True)\n                                 .quantile(mhw_threshold*0.01, dim = 'time', skipna = True))\n\n    return da_data_quantile\n","visibility":"show","key":"C9CaoC75GF"},{"type":"output","id":"Z5rgp-2133t5AnTrqUz4A","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"KXDeNtJdeH"}],"visibility":"show","key":"iG4aNZNiKR"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"%time da_mon_quantile = mj_3mon_quantile(ds_mon_anom.sst, mhw_threshold=90)","visibility":"show","key":"jOVbfazZmt"},{"type":"output","id":"2TMbshwgFF2qbgf4iAOEC","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"MOc8jskv88"}],"visibility":"show","key":"M5M8PyumYD"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"div","class":"admonition alert alert-info","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Tip","key":"tVKMb2x9yy"}],"key":"NAEMElD1K5"},{"type":"text","value":"The `%time` command is jupyter cell magic to time the one-liner cell operation. It provides a great way to find the bottleneck of your data processing steps.","key":"jIOpvuBfLz"}],"key":"jY7hzLxX3D"}],"key":"GGCrh6x05X"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The determined threshold value of each grid of each month is shown below","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"UM458CGQqG"}],"key":"qEESkDzHWs"}],"key":"cYqryQuy0Q"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"da_mon_quantile.isel(month=0).plot(vmin=0,vmax=3)","visibility":"show","key":"erJyHLLvUl"},{"type":"output","id":"2k0hJs_5BSMOLtJ6tMrXk","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"Adhb9SAUG4"}],"visibility":"show","key":"oYXKnHkcwa"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Identify the marine heatwaves based on threshold","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"VZosAiEXaC"}],"identifier":"identify-the-marine-heatwaves-based-on-threshold","label":"Identify the marine heatwaves based on threshold","html_id":"identify-the-marine-heatwaves-based-on-threshold","implicit":true,"key":"jOh659onGh"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The figure below shows the original SST anomaly value for the first month.","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"key":"U78m1P1j2R"}],"key":"QSOa9AexHD"}],"key":"nq5kNDQKUS"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"ds_mon_anom.sst.isel(time=0).plot(vmin=0,vmax=3)","visibility":"show","key":"XvWOIdApYx"},{"type":"output","id":"plMamoInViRtcs5Jniy5z","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"UHgeXoZGcU"}],"visibility":"show","key":"Yd0rb5zVhr"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To identify the marine heatwaves based on the monthly threshold, we use the ","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"T7IBMO8QWb"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"where","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"NR2aYrYa9M"},{"type":"text","value":" method to find the monthly marine heatwaves with the grid that has SST anomaly below the threshold to be masked as Not-a-Number.","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"VzIVDpXeFS"}],"key":"pOlfGycnXj"}],"key":"lVJdy4NWsI"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"da_mhw = ds_mon_anom.sst.where(ds_mon_anom.sst.groupby('time.month')>da_mon_quantile)","visibility":"show","key":"rJdO7DZaP4"},{"type":"output","id":"NpEnGXYYZJA9pGFMdOlVJ","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"O2e43kHsHW"}],"visibility":"show","key":"u0QjSLKAbb"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The figure below shows the SST anomalous values that are above the monthly thresholds for the first months.","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"xlpQCOToti"}],"key":"Z01ithB2Hh"}],"visibility":"show","key":"uqYwTTuEJB"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"da_mhw.isel(time=0).plot(vmin=0,vmax=3)","visibility":"show","key":"ezQePuwCdT"},{"type":"output","id":"aJdYv98OUmfw5QyB8nph7","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"sAdc5ywMmm"}],"visibility":"show","key":"e01J6LUbPm"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Interactive plot","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"t9YgtBWrM8"}],"identifier":"interactive-plot","label":"Interactive plot","html_id":"interactive-plot","implicit":true,"key":"LmoFDQagoH"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The interactive plot is a great tool for looking at a local changes through zoom in.\nPlotly provides a great interface for the user to also pin point the actual value at the point where they are interested in.\nThe only thing that need further data manipulation for using the plotly tool is to convert the Xarray DataArray to Pandas DataFrame.\nHowever, this can be easily achieved throught the method ","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"key":"uG6XDU0bAN"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":".to_dataframe()","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"key":"scFKv7yuPG"},{"type":"text","value":" provided by the Xarray package.","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"key":"AHZABLmNjk"}],"key":"ujURGWIcaQ"}],"key":"aNu0ZmBYLZ"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"dff = (da_mhw.isel(time=0)\n             .to_dataframe()\n             .reset_index()\n             .dropna()\n      )\n\ndff = dff.rename(columns={'sst':'MHW magnitude'})","key":"lIGkkfdIn6"},{"type":"output","id":"Q_0_mdtzfB7AXfg-5Uu-J","data":[],"key":"ZIMgSCSEw7"}],"key":"NG1kEpbGKs"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Plotly setting","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"jEPiC8k8W8"}],"identifier":"plotly-setting","label":"Plotly setting","html_id":"plotly-setting","implicit":true,"key":"HkRsXNUtUf"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After the DataFrame is created the plotly map can be created. Here, we are only using some simple options. More detail setups and options can be find on the ","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"key":"mkrl9saUv2"},{"type":"link","url":"https://plotly.com/python/scattermapbox/","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Plotly documentation","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"key":"KnnYGdJXKc"}],"urlSource":"https://plotly.com/python/scattermapbox/","key":"pZ8aya21J5"}],"key":"mrLGyAeIQc"}],"key":"sDpTnfC4UV"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"# Setup the scatter mapbox detail\ncenter = {'lat':38,'lon':-94}   # center of the map\nzoom = 2                        # zoom level of the map\nmarker_size = 8                 # marker size used on the map\nmapbox_style = 'carto-positron' # mapbox options\n\nfig = px.scatter_mapbox(dff,\n    lon = 'lon',\n    lat = 'lat',\n    color = 'MHW magnitude',\n    color_continuous_scale = 'orrd'\n)\n\nfig.update_layout(\n    mapbox={\n        'style': mapbox_style,\n        'center': center,\n        'zoom': zoom,\n    }\n)\n\n\n# Update the marker size using update_traces\nfig.update_traces(marker=dict(size=marker_size))\n","visibility":"show","key":"rjziF7jMXr"},{"type":"output","id":"Cr2PW0Pt4HNm_nlrN311g","data":[],"visibility":"show","key":"yYRyybCK61"}],"visibility":"show","key":"FtiROvb4bn"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"thematicBreak","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"vLTPC7u15Q"}],"key":"BQXqB5D29t"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"